{"title_page": "Deaths in October 2006", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{Deaths in month TOC}}\n\nThe following is a list of notable '''deaths in October 2006'''.\n\nEntries for each day are listed <u>alphabetically</u> by surname. A typical entry lists information in the following sequence:\n* Name, age, country of citizenship at birth, subsequent country of citizenship (if applicable), reason for notability, cause of death (if known), and reference.\n<!--\n \n* * * * * * * Please adhere to the guidelines below when adding a name to this article. * * * * * * *\n\n(1) Please add only those meeting Wikipedia notability guidelines. Please include a reference to a reliable source. If a Wikipedia article for the deceased does not yet exist, please reconsider whether the subject is actually notable. If so, please consider writing an article yourself. Those without a Wikipedia article are removed after one month.\n\n(2) Please understand that the intent of this article is to report notable deaths. Tragic deaths, while unfortunate, do not necessarily render the deceased \"notable\". If you report the death of a subject that does not already have a Wikipedia article, please consider starting one, provided that the deceased is notable. Please include third-party sources other than the obituary.\n\n(3) Please add entries in alphabetical order by family name. Please avoid overlinking. As such, please do not add links to nationalities, common occupations, or common causes of death. Rather, please include only \"links that aid navigation and understanding\". Thank you.\n\n(4) References should be in <ref>[url & title]</ref> format, as full citations make the page too slow to load, and too big to edit.\n\n* * * * * * * Please adhere to the guidelines above when adding a name to this article * * * * * * *\n\n--->\n\n==October 2006==\n\n===1===\n*[[Frank Beyer]], 74, German film director (''[[Jacob the Liar]]'').<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/03/obituaries/03beyer.html |title=Frank Beyer, 74, East German Who Directed 'Jacob the Liar,' Dies |date=3 October 2006 |agency=Agence France-Presse |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Laurence Brodie-Hall|Sir Laurence Brodie-Hall]], 96, Australian mining executive.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2006-10-02/wa-mining-great-brodie-hall-dies/1276342 |title=WA mining great Brodie-Hall dies |date=2 October 2006 |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Alan Caillou]], 91, British actor and writer.<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://variety.com/2006/scene/markets-festivals/alan-caillou-1117951207/ |title=Alan Caillou |date=3 October 2006 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Pierre Gorman]], 82, Australian librarian and academic.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://archive.uninews.unimelb.edu.au/news/3786/ |title=Vale Pierre Patrick Gorman (1924\u20132006) |date=30 October 2006 |website=University of Melbourne |accessdate=3 December 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131207025921/http://archive.uninews.unimelb.edu.au/news/3786/ |archivedate=7 December 2013 }}</ref> \n*[[Jack Kirkbride]], 83, British cartoonist, father of actress [[Anne Kirkbride]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/tm_headline=corrie-s-anne-mourns-her-dad-&method=full&objectid=17873966&siteid=66633-name_page.html |date=5 October 2006 |title=Corrie's Anne Mourns Her Dad |newspaper=[[Daily Record (Scotland)|Daily Record]] |access-date=4 April 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070930015059/http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/tm_headline=corrie-s-anne-mourns-her-dad-&method=full&objectid=17873966&siteid=66633-name_page.html |archive-date=30 September 2007}}</ref>\n*[[Anna Kunkel]], 74, American baseball player ([[All-American Girls Professional Baseball League|AAGPBL]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.aagpbl.org/