 Dies |website=PR-Inside.com |access-date=4 April 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081007194348/http://www.pr-inside.com/entertainment-blog/2006/10/04/frances-bergen-dies/ |archive-date=7 October 2008}}</ref>\n*[[Helen Chenoweth-Hage]], 68, American Republican Representative for Idaho (1995\u20132001), car accident.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/15111030/ |title=Former U.S. Rep. Chenoweth-Hage dies |date=3 October 2006 |website=[[NBC News]] |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Bhaktisvarupa Damodar Swami]], 69, Indian scientist, spiritual teacher and poet, heart attack.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vina.cc/2006/10/03/srila-b-s-damodar-maharaja-leaves-the-world/ |title=Srila B.S. Damodar Maharaja Leaves the World |date=3 October 2006 |website=World Vaisnava Association |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Tamara Dobson]], 59, American actress (''[[Cleopatra Jones]]''), complications from pneumonia and multiple sclerosis.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/10/05/AR2006100501794.html |title=Tamara Dobson, 59; 'Cleopatra Jones' Star |date=6 October 2006 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Halmos]], 90, Hungarian-born American mathematician.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/20/obituaries/20halmos.html |title=Paul Halmos, 90, Mathematician Known for Simplifying Concepts, Dies |first=Jeremy |last=Pearce |date=20 October 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Paul Richardson (organist)|Paul Richardson]], 74, American [[Philadelphia Phillies|Phillies]] longtime organist, prostate cancer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cbs.sportsline.com/mlb/story/9703334 |title=Phillies longtime organist Richardson dies at 74 |date=3 October 2006 |website=[[CBS SportsLine]] |accessdate=1 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061011192505/http://cbs.sportsline.com/mlb/story/9703334 |archivedate=11 October 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Clyde Vollmer]], 85, American Major League Baseball player ([[Cincinnati Reds]]).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sabr.org/bioproj/person/c844a005 |last=Greene |first=Nelson 'Chip' |title=Clyde Vollmer |website=[[Society for American Baseball Research]] |access-date=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n===3===\n*[[Lucilla Andrews]], 86, British romantic novelist.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/default_content/12499232.Lucilla_Andrews/ |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 October 2006 |title=Lucilla Andrews |newspaper=[[The Herald (Glasgow)|The Herald]] |access-date=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[John Cox (admiral)|Sir John Cox]], 77, British admiral who was Commander-in-Chief in the South Atlantic.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1531196/Vice-Admiral-Sir-John-Cox.html |title=Vice-Admiral Sir John Cox |date=12 October 2006 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[John Crank]], 90, British mathematical physicist who helped solve the [[heat equation]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1533100/Professor-John-Crank.html |title=Professor John Crank |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Gwen Meredith]], 98, Australian writer of all 5795 episodes of the long-running radio serial ''[[Blue Hills (radio serial)|Blue Hills]]'', after heart trouble.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2006-10-04/blue-hills-writer-dies/1278498 |date=4 October 2006 |title='Blue Hills' writer dies |website=[[ABC News (Australia)|ABC News]] |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Peter Norman]], 64, Australian athlete, silver medalist at the [[1968 Summer Olympics]], heart attack.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/04/sports/othersports/04norman.html |title=Peter Norman, 64, Who Shared Podium at '68 Games, Dies |date=4 October 2006 |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n===4===\n\n*[[R. W. Apple, Jr.]], 71, American political journalist and food writer (''[[The New York Times]]''), thoracic cancer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cnn.com/2006/POLITICS/10/04/obit.apple.ap/index.html |title=Longtime New York Times correspondent R.W. Apple dies |date=4 October 2006 |website=CNN |accessdate=1 November 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061103014206/http://www.cnn.com/2006/POLITICS/10/04/obit.apple.ap/index.html |archivedate=3 November 2006}}</ref>\n*[[Tom Bell (actor)|Tom Bell]], 73, British actor (''[[Wish You Were Here (1987 film)|Wish You Were Here]]'', ''[[Prime Suspect (UK TV series)|Prime Suspect]]''), after short illness.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1530776/Tom-Bell.html |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=7 October 2006 |title=Tom Bell |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Victor Dyrgall]], 88, American Olympic runner.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/dy/vic-dyrgall-1.html |title=Vic Dyrgall |website=[[Sports Reference]] |access-date=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Franti\u0161ek Fajtl]], 94, Czech World War II fighter pilot, after long illness.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1531002/Major-General-Frantisek-Fajtl.html |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=10 October 2006 |title=Major General Frantisek Fajtl |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |access-date=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Norbert Franck]], 88, Luxembourgian Olympic swimmer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/fr/norbert-franck-1.html |title=Norbert Franck |website=Sports Reference |accessdate=4 April 2018}}</ref>\n*[[Walter Gibb]], 87, British aviator and test pilot who twice held the world [[flight altitude record]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1532373/Wing-Commander-Walter-Gibb.html |title=Wing Commander Walter G